Automation Strategy
What should be automated
Navigation links (KickAndBoom, BacanaGol, 18+ Portal).
CTA buttons (Play Now, Continue).
Loading of game pages.
Recommendation section ("You Might Like").
Responsive behavior on desktop/tablet/mobile.
Visual regression of the main page layout.
Analytics events (click on Play Now, Continue).
Smoke and regression tests for critical user flows.

What should remain manual
Exploratory testing.
UX and usability validation.
Ad/banner content verification.
New game content validation.
Subjective visual reviews.

Recommended tools/frameworks
Selenide + Java for UI automation.
Selenide for visual regression.
Allure Reports for reporting.
GitHub Actions or Jenkins for CI/CD.

Integration into development/release process
Run smoke tests on every Pull Request.
Run full regression suite nightly.
Execute visual regression tests before releases.
Block deployment if critical automated tests fail.
Run post-deployment smoke tests in staging/production.

After release:
Automated smoke tests in production/staging
Monitoring and alert validation
Health-check APIs
